			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerTitleCompanyLabel">Creative Director, Play, a division of Denuo</span></td>
		        </tr>
		        <tr>
			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerBioLabel">As a founding member and creative director for Play, the first agency to leverage videogames as a marketing contact point, McCarthy is a translator, integrator and guide for brands into the gaming space.  His work for clients ensures videogame content personifies the brand's attributes and mirrors its values and personality while providing value to consumers.  During his extensive work in the digital and gaming arena, McCarthy has mastered strategic brand messaging on behalf of clients such as GM, Kellogg's, P&G and the U.S. Army.

Prior to joining Play, McCarthy worked at Chemistri/iLeo as the lead designer on goarmy.com website. As part of the U.S. Army's new identity launch in 2001, McCarthy created multiple online advertising campaigns to drive traffic to the site. Accolades for this project include: an EFFIE award, a Cannes Bronze Cyber Lion and a One Show Silver Pencil.</span></td>
